### [Luke Chapter 6](../../../bib/kjv/luk006.htm#001.md)

[Luke 6:1](../../../bib/kjv/luk006.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">luk 6:1</span></span>

The first Sabbath - So the Jews reckoned their Sabbaths, from the
passover to pentecost; the first, second, third, and so on, till the
seventh Sabbath (after the second day.) This immediately preceded
pentecost, which was the fiftieth day after the second day of unleavened
bread. [Mat 12:1](../../../bib/kjv/mat012.htm#001.md); [Mar
2:23](../../../bib/kjv/mar002.htm#023.md).

[Luke 6:2](../../../bib/kjv/luk006.htm#002.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_002">luk 6:2</span></span>

Why do ye - St. Matthew and Mark represent the Pharisees as proposing
the question to our Lord himself. It was afterward, probably, they
proposed it to his disciples.

