or happiness therein.

[Luke 6:25](../../../bib/kjv/luk006.htm#025.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_025">luk 6:25</span></span>

Full - Of meat and drink, and worldly goods. That laugh - That are of a
light trifling spirit.

[Luke 6:26](../../../bib/kjv/luk006.htm#026.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_026">luk 6:26</span></span>

Wo to you when all men shall speak well of you - But who will believe
this?

[Luke 6:27](../../../bib/kjv/luk006.htm#027.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_027">luk 6:27</span></span>

But I say to you that hear - Hitherto our Lord had spoken only to
particular sorts of persons: now he begins speaking to all in general.
[Mat 5:44](../../../bib/kjv/mat005.htm#044.md).

[Luke 6:29](../../../bib/kjv/luk006.htm#029.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_029">luk 6:29</span></span>

To him that smiteth thee on the cheek - Taketh away thy cloak - These
seem to be proverbial expressions, to signify an invasion of the
tenderest points of honour and property. Offer the other - Forbid not
thy coat - That is, rather yield to his repeating the affront or injury,
than gratify resentment in righting your self; in any method not
becoming Christian love. [Mat 5:39](../../../bib/kjv/mat005.htm#039.md).

[Luke 6:30](../../../bib/kjv/luk006.htm#030.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_030">luk 6:30</span></span>

Give to every one - Friend or enemy, what thou canst spare, and he
really wants: and of him that taketh away thy goods - By borrowing, if
he be insolvent, ask them not again. [Mat
5:42](../../../bib/kjv/mat005.htm#042.md).

